itals, universities, and health care conferences all over the United States, Bedside Manners invariably sparks a vibrant conversation about patient safety problems and how to solve them, job satisfaction and stress, and the importance of information sharing and mutual respect. As text or script, this play is a unique teaching tool for medical and nursing schools, and other health professional schools and continuing education programs involving health care clinicians and staff of all kinds.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCommunication in medicine. 0aDrama in education. 0aHealth care teams. 0aMedical personnelxTraining of. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 4aMedicine & Medical Issues. 7aMEDICAL / Nursing / Nurse & Patient.2bisacsh  abehavior changes, play acting, interprofessional cooperation, health care cooperation, poor communication, hospital errors, workplace relations, patient care quality.1 aGordon, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayes, Lisa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHayes, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeape, Lucian L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReeves, Scott, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aReeves, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080146922040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801469220423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801469220/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aE